Copyright.AdditionalInfo: The survey consisted of NIMS long period sites and collocated MT24 short period sites. The collocated sites shared the same E lines but used different magnetic field sensors. Site numbering conventions were as follows: CAY2__ - NIMS long period instruments CAY1__ - short period MT24 instruments Collocated MT24 and NIMS sites from Sierran study (CAW, CAX, CAY) have same site numbers EXCEPT for first number. NIMS sites were tagged with 2nn and MT24 sites were tagged with 1nn. Example: CAX201 is a NIMS site at CAXn01 location and CAX101 is an MT24 site at CAXn01 site. Collocated sites used the same electrodes and dipoles for electric field measurements. In a few locations, only MT24 data were collected. These sites have names like caw110rr1.edi for a remote reference station at caw110 location. EDI files for MT24 consist of merged MT impedances and tensors from 3 recording bands. Sites with both NIMS and MT24 data were merged to produce single broadband and long period site response. All processing was done with Larsen's robust processing code (1996).A frequency dependence of exp(-jwt) is assumed for the FFT used in the transfer function calculation by Larsen's code (this corresponds to assuming that the signal has time dependence exp(+iwt) in the forward modeling code), and remote referencing was used for the majority of the stations The MT24 and NIMS data were processed separately to the point of generating impedances and Hz transfer functions. Regardless of sensor orientation, tensor coordinates were rotated to x = geographic north and y = geographic east. .
